## 2026-04-03 - BatchEditor cannot batch-replace alias references
- Added an "Alias replace" sub-mode to the divider section of `BatchEditor.tsx`. Users enter a source alias path (e.g. `color.primary`) and a target path (e.g. `brand.primary`) — the tool finds all selected tokens where `$value` contains `{color.primary}` as a substring and rewrites them to `{brand.primary}`. Supports partial path matches (handles embedded refs in composite values). Shows a preview box listing affected tokens with from→to pairs before committing. Calls the existing `batch-update` API endpoint and pushes an undo slot via `onPushUndo`.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/BatchEditor.tsx` ~L92 (state), ~L278 (memo), ~L557 (handler), ~L1010 (JSX)
