## 2026-04-03 - SelectionInspector has no "apply to all matching properties" action
- Added a `propTypeSuggestion` state to `SelectionInspector.tsx` that tracks a pending "Apply to all [type] properties" suggestion. After binding a token to any property, the handler detects other visible unbound properties that accept the same token type (e.g., after binding a color token to `fill`, it finds `stroke` and any other unbound color properties). If any exist, a persistent banner appears at the bottom of the inspector with the token path, token type label, a comma-separated list of affected property names, an "Apply to all" button, and a dismiss button. Clicking "Apply to all" sends an `apply-to-selection` plugin message for each target property. The suggestion is cleared on selection change or when dismissed.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/SelectionInspector.tsx` ~L14 (import), ~L204 (state), ~L320 (clear in effect), ~L467 (detection in handleBindToken), ~L1030 (banner UI)
